  "body": "Consider the following contract:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED\r\npragma solidity =0.7.6;\r\n\r\ncontract C {\r\n    uint public           A;\r\n    uint public           B;\r\n    constructor() {\r\n        A = 5;\r\n    }\r\n    function setB(uint _B) public {\r\n        B = _B;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nconstructing this contract, as well as calling `setB(8)` both result in transactions that when the `Debug` button is clicked, there exist steps where at least one of the Function Stack, Solidity Locals and Solidity State fields are non-empty.\r\n\r\nHowever, for the following contract:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED\r\npragma solidity =0.7.6;\r\n\r\ncontract C {\r\n    uint public immutable A;\r\n    uint public           B;\r\n    constructor() {\r\n        A = 5;\r\n    }\r\n    function setB(uint _B) public {\r\n        B = _B;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n(A is made immutable), that is not the case. During construction the fields \"work\", but when `setB(8)` is called, all three of the above fields are empty for the entire duration of the call. This is unexpected behavior; any ideas what is causing this? Thanks.",
